reviews.review_text: the unknown taper his name was jim.as i groveled for the patch, he was more then gracious.we were the closest tapers to the stage.about 25 feet.there was a graveyard of mics as i remember.the next show at rochester there was no fob recordings allowed.what sucked even more i got there late and wasn't about to scumb bag my way up front.i would have gone stealth for sure.imo hampton 84 2nd night had the best sound out of any year they played there.highlights for me @ this show are stranger,intro into touch.dew,throwin stones{the new way}and the all time best belting out of baby blue that jerry ever played,bar none imo!!!! get this 2nd set

hey i would wager my 2 TB hard-drive full of shows that the "Jim" you speak of, the "unknown taper" who hooked you up was none other than the renowned master taper of all tape masters, mr. Jim Vita rip jimmy.

your old friend david, and thanks for all the great tapes !!!
